  "texts": [
    "Additionally, pooling reduces memory consumption, manages computational costs and weights, and mitigates overfitting.",
    "The most common pooling methods include max pooling and average pooling.",
    "In max pooling, the highest value within a specified region of the input feature is selected as the output for that region, thereby emphasizing prominent features.",
    "Conversely, average pooling calculates the average value from a specific region of the input feature map to produce a smoother representation of features within that region.",
    "This approach aids in locating objects in images while considering their overall appearance."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}